item.title: Simon Denny - Dotcom Séance | Outernet
item.description: The bombastically-named, black-and-gold clad Now Building is the West End’s newest (and brightest) art gallery. Opened a couple of weeks ago opposite Tottenham Court Road tube station, the open-plan space glows from within, thanks to the massive LED screens that blaze across its interior walls and ceiling. It’s part of a newly-opened complex called the Outernet, which also includes a new theatre and the restoration of a very useful pathway to Soho Square.
